Abstraction:
 is the process of exposing the essential details of an entity, 
 while ignoring the irrelevant details, 
 to reduce the complexity for the users.

Encapsulation:
 is the process of bundling data and operations 
 on the data together in an entity.

Inheritance:
 is used to derive a new type from an existing type, 
 thereby establishing a parent-child relationship.

Polymorphism:
 lets an entity take on different meanings in different contexts.